<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading page-header" lang="en"><span dir="auto">List of characters</span></h1>

<div id="bodyContent">
<div id="siteSub">From A Wiki of Ice and Fire</div>
<div id="contentSub"></div>
<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
Jump to: <a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, <a href="#p-search">search</a>
</div>
<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table border="0" class="toccolours plainlinks">
<tbody><tr>
<th>Contents:
</th>
<td><b><a href="#A">A</a> <a href="#B">B</a> <a href="#C">C</a> <a href="#D">D</a> <a href="#E">E</a> <a href="#F">F</a> <a href="#G">G</a> <a href="#H">H</a> <a href="#I">I</a> <a href="#J">J</a> <a href="#K">K</a> <a href="#L">L</a> <a href="#M">M</a> <a href="#N">N</a> <a href="#O">O</a> <a href="#P">P</a> <a href="#Q">Q</a> <a href="#R">R</a> <a href="#S">S</a> <a href="#T">T</a> <a href="#U">U</a> <a href="#V">V</a> <a href="#W">W</a> <a href="#X">X</a> <a href="#Y">Y</a> <a href="#Z">Z</a></b>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p><br />
This page lists all characters from the <i>A Song of Ice and Fire</i> series alphabetically according to the characters’ first names, regardless of if the character is better known by a nickname. For example: <a href="/index.php/Sour_Alyn" title="Sour Alyn">Sour Alyn</a> is listed under "A" for Alyn and not "S" for Sour. If possible, unnamed characters are listed under their House name. For example: <a href="/index.php/Lord_Redwyne" title="Lord Redwyne">Lord Redwyne</a> is under "R". Characters that exist only in material outside the novels and are of dubious or no canonicity are marked by bold text.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="A">A</span></h3>
<ul><li><a href="/index.php/A_certain_man" title="A certain man">A certain man</a></li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Abelar_Hightower" title="Abelar Hightower">Abelar Hightower</a>, challenger at the <a href="/index.php/Tourney_at_Ashford_Meadow" title="Tourney at Ashford Meadow">tourney at Ashford Meadow</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Abelon" title="Abelon">Abelon</a>, an archmaester.</li>
<li><b><a href="/index.php/Aberdolf_Strongbeard" title="Aberdolf Strongbeard">Aberdolf Strongbeard</a></b></li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_of_Duskendale" title="Addam of Duskendale">Addam of Duskendale</a>, a merchant.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Frey" title="Addam Frey">Addam Frey</a>, a knight at the <a href="/index.php/Whitewalls_tourney" class="mw-redirect" title="Whitewalls tourney">Whitewalls tourney</a>, cousin to Lady Butterwell.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Hightower" title="Addam Hightower">Addam Hightower</a>, a Lord of Oldtown.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Marbrand" title="Addam Marbrand">Addam Marbrand</a>, a knight in the service of <a href="/index.php/House_Lannister" title="House Lannister">House Lannister</a>. Heir to Ashemark.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Osgrey" title="Addam Osgrey">Addam Osgrey</a>, son of Eustace Osgrey, slain on the Redgrass Field during the <a href="/index.php/First_Blackfyre_Rebellion" title="First Blackfyre Rebellion">First Blackfyre Rebellion</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Rivers" title="Addam Rivers">Addam Rivers</a>, a knight who claimed the title of King of the Trident.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Velaryon" title="Addam Velaryon">Addam Velaryon</a>, a dragonrider during the <a href="/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons" title="Dance of the Dragons">Dance of the Dragons</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addam_Whitehead" title="Addam Whitehead">Addam Whitehead</a>, the heir of Weeping Town.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Addison_Hill" title="Addison Hill">Addison Hill</a>, a former member of the <a href="/index.php/Kingsguard" title="Kingsguard">Kingsguard</a>.</li>
<li><b><a href="/index.php?title=Adham_Dannett&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Adham Dannett (page does not exist)">Adham Dannett</a></b></li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Adrack_Humble" title="Adrack Humble">Adrack Humble</a>, an ironborn raider.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Adrian_Redfort" title="Adrian Redfort">Adrian Redfort</a>, a member of the Kingsguard.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Adrian_Tarbeck" title="Adrian Tarbeck">Adrian Tarbeck</a>, a knight during the Dance of the Dragons.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Adrian_Thorne" title="Adrian Thorne">Adrian Thorne</a>, a Commander of the City Watch of King's Landing.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Ambrose" title="Aegon Ambrose">Aegon Ambrose</a></li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre" title="Aegon Blackfyre">Aegon Blackfyre</a>, son of Daemon Blackfyre, killed at the Redgrass Field during the Blackfyre Rebellion.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Frey_(son_of_Stevron)" title="Aegon Frey (son of Stevron)">Aegon Frey</a>, called Jinglebell. A halfwit fool at the Twins, killed by Catelyn Stark.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Frey_(son_of_Aenys)" title="Aegon Frey (son of Aenys)">Aegon Frey</a>, called Bloodborn. Eldest son of Ser Aenys Frey. <a href="/index.php/Outlaw" class="mw-redirect" title="Outlaw">Outlaw</a> of the <a href="/index.php/Riverlands" title="Riverlands">riverlands</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen" title="Aegon I Targaryen">Aegon I Targaryen</a>, called the Conqueror. First King of the <a href="/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms" title="Seven Kingdoms">Seven Kingdoms</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen" title="Aegon II Targaryen">Aegon II Targaryen</a>, killed in the <a href="/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons" title="Dance of the Dragons">Dance of the Dragons</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen" title="Aegon III Targaryen">Aegon III Targaryen</a>, called the Dragonslayer and Dragonsbane.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen" title="Aegon IV Targaryen">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>, called the Unworthy.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen" title="Aegon V Targaryen">Aegon V Targaryen</a>, called Egg and the Unlikely.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Gaemon)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Gaemon)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, a Lord of Dragonstone during the Century of Blood.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Aenys_I)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Aenys I)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, eldest son of King Aenys I Targaryen</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Jaehaerys_I)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Jaehaerys I)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, eldest son of King Jaehaerys I and Queen Alysanne. Died young.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Baelon)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Baelon)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, youngest son of Prince Baelon Targaryen</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Aerys_II)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Aerys II)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, third son of King Aerys II and Queen Rhaella Targaryen.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegon_Targaryen_(son_of_Rhaegar)" title="Aegon Targaryen (son of Rhaegar)">Aegon Targaryen</a>, infant son of Rhaegar. Killed during the <a href="/index.php/Sack_of_King%27s_Landing" title="Sack of King&#39;s Landing">Sack of King's Landing</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aegor_Rivers" title="Aegor Rivers">Aegor Rivers</a>, called "Bittersteel". A legitimized bastard of Aegon IV and rebel to the throne.</li>
<li><b><a href="/index.php/Aelinor_Targaryen" title="Aelinor Targaryen">Aelinor Targaryen</a></b></li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aelinor_Penrose" title="Aelinor Penrose">Aelinor Penrose</a>, queen to Aerys I.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aelor_Targaryen" title="Aelor Targaryen">Aelor Targaryen</a>, the son of Prince Rhaegel Targaryen.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aelora_Targaryen" title="Aelora Targaryen">Aelora Targaryen</a>, the daughter of Prince Rhaegel Targaryen.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aelyx_Targaryen" title="Aelyx Targaryen">Aelyx Targaryen</a>, a Lord of Dragonstone during the Century of Blood.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aemma_Arryn" title="Aemma Arryn">Aemma Arryn</a>, daughter of Lord Arryn and Princess <a href="/index.php/Daella_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Jaehaerys_I)" title="Daella Targaryen (daughter of Jaehaerys I)">Daella Targaryen</a>, first wife to King <a href="/index.php/Viserys_I_Targaryen" title="Viserys I Targaryen">Viserys I Targaryen</a>, mother of Queen <a href="/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen" title="Rhaenyra Targaryen">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre" title="Aemon Blackfyre">Aemon Blackfyre</a>, son of Daemon Blackfyre, killed at the Redgrass Field during the Blackfyre Rebellion.</li>
